ActFinancial Administration Act
SubjectRegulations Amending the Licensed Dealers for Controlled Drugs and Narcotics Fees Regulations (1056)
PrecisRegulations Amending the LICENSED DEALERS FOR CONTROLLED DRUGS AND NARCOTICS FEES REGULATIONS (1056), in order to limit the application of the regulations to dealer's licences for controlled drugs and narcotics for veterinary use only. These Regulations will exempt publicly-funded health care facilities or any branch or agency of federal and provincial governments from fees for dealer’s licences. Additionally, persons or organizations solely conducting scientific investigations will also be excluded from fees associated with dealer’s licences.
